participating-org.narrative:
Founded on April 08 2008, VACR is non-government organization working on the protection of child#s rights, with the mission to gather and unite Vietnamese individuals and organizations who voluntarily working for the purpose of making children enjoy all fundamental rights.
Our six key mandates are:
(1) Promoting advocacy and providing consultancy to improve capacity on child protection;
(2) Participating in supervising, evaluating child rights implementation;
(3) Formulating and implementing programs, projects# to protectchildren;
(4) Carrying out cooperation research, training and information/experience sharing;
(5) Mobilizing children#s voice and participation; and
(6) Becoming focal point between INGO, CSOs and GO agencies.
